# Web UI conventions

## Stack

Vite, React 19, React Router, Mantine 9, Tabler icons. No extra UI libraries.

## Structure

```
web/src/
├── pages/          # Settings, Repositories, Skills, Agents, ArtifactListPage
├── components/     # ArtifactCard, ArtifactCardGrid, artifactRow helpers
└── api/client.ts   # fetch wrapper; JSON Content-Type only when body present
```

## Copy language

- All user-facing UI strings in `web/` (labels, titles, placeholders, alerts, empty states) must be **simple English** only.
- Do not translate the interface to Russian or any other language unless the user explicitly asks for i18n/l10n work.

## UX rules

- **Global** / **Project** icons are independent toggles; both may be on; click applies immediately (no Save button).
- Click active icon → deactivate (remove symlink only; never delete repo/catalog files).
- `defaultProjectPath` from `/api/status` (CLI cwd) is the only project install path; read-only in UI. Saved `projectPath` in config when project is off is kept for symlink removal only.
- Cards: max 480px, grid `auto-fill` in `ArtifactCardGrid`.
- Scope from frontmatter disables toggles; blocked paths (non-symlink exists) disable toggles.
- Agent cards list `skillDependencies` with description tooltips; skill toggles stay disabled while a dependent agent is installed.
- Turning off **global** or **project** on an agent (each scope separately): if dependent skills are installed in that scope and unused by other agents in the same scope, modal offers optional skill removal for that scope only (checkboxes, default off).
- Match installations and row patches by `repoId` + `kind` + `artifactId` (skill and agent may share the same id string, e.g. `article-architect`); UI row key is `kind:id`.

## Dev

`npm run dev` — server :3921 + Vite :5173 with `/api` proxy.

## Tests (required)

After any change under `web/` (components, pages, install/uninstall UX, `artifactRow` helpers), **run before finishing**:

```bash
npm run test:web
```

Add or update tests in `web/src/**/*.test.ts` when behavior changes (install scopes, agent/skill id collisions, deletable dependents, patches). Do not merge web UX logic changes without green tests.
